2006: A 6.8 magnitude earthquake reached southern Java, Indonesia's most inhabited island, triggering a tsunami that struck the south coast and struck nearly 700 victims.
2009: A 7.6 magnitude earthquake shook the city of Padang, capital of the province of West Sumatra.
More than 1,100 people were killed.
2010: A 7.5 magnitude earthquake devastated one of the Mentawai Islands off Sumatra and triggered a tsunami of over 10 metres that destroyed dozens of villages and killed about 300 people.
2016: A superficial earthquake shook the resistance of Pidie Jaya to Aceh, causing destruction and panic, reminding the inhabitants of the devastation caused by the earthquake and the 2004 deadly tsunami.
